Kenya road crash toll up The death toll in the crash involving a passenger bus and a truck on the Nakuru-Eldoret highway in western Kenya rises to nine after two people succumb to injuries at Eldama Ravine Sub-County Hospital. Somali envoy back home Somalia's ambassador to Kenya Mohamoud Ahmed Nur alias Tarzan arrives in Mogadishu following his expulsion by the Kenya government, which also recalled its envoy to the neighbouring state, Lt-Gen (Rtd) Lucas Tumbov. Gaddafi fall remembered Its the eighth anniversary of revolt that brought down former Libyan strong man Muammar Gaddafi's dictatorship. Mozambique's royal arrest The son of Mozambique's former President Armando Guebuza, Mr Ndambi Guebuza, under arrest over the country's hidden debts scandal. Call for calm in Nigeria Nigeria's President Muhammadu Buhari and leading opposition candidate Atiku Abubakar appeal for calm after the shock move to delay elections for a week. Zimbabwe mine tragedy Search continues for survivors and bodies following the flooding of an illegal gold mine in Zimbabwe on last Tuesday night. The Cameroon crisis The humanitarian crisis worsens in the restive English-speaking Northwest and Southwest Cameroon where the number of the Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) has surged.   Nairobi says ambassador told to return to Mogadishu for consultations Delegates says secret ballot less transparent